## Environmental and Physical Impacts

Climate change manifests through various environmental changes that pose direct and indirect threats to ecosystems and human societies:

- **Temperature Rise and Heatwaves**: Global temperatures have increased, leading to more frequent and intense heatwaves. This exacerbates drought conditions and contributes to the expansion of deserts ([Wikipedia, 2024](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climate_change)).

- **Melting Ice and Sea Level Rise**: Arctic warming has accelerated melting of permafrost, glaciers, and sea ice, contributing to rising sea levels. This threatens coastal communities and low-lying island nations with flooding and land loss ([Wikipedia, 2024](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climate_change)).

- **Extreme Weather Events**: Increased temperatures intensify storms, hurricanes, wildfires, and droughts, causing widespread destruction and displacement ([Wikipedia, 2024](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climate_change)).

- **Biodiversity Loss**: Rapid environmental changes force many species to relocate or face extinction, disrupting ecosystems and the services they provide, such as pollination, water purification, and carbon sequestration ([Smale et al., 2019](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Climate_change)).

| Environmental Impact       | Description                                         | Consequence                                      |
|---------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------|
| Heatwaves and Desertification | Increased frequency and severity of heatwaves and desert expansion | Reduced agricultural productivity, water scarcity |
| Melting Ice and Sea Level Rise | Loss of glaciers and sea ice, rising oceans | Coastal flooding, habitat loss, displacement     |
| Extreme Weather Events     | More intense storms, droughts, and wildfires       | Infrastructure damage, economic loss, human displacement |
| Biodiversity Loss         | Species relocation/extinction due to habitat changes | Ecosystem disruption, loss of ecosystem services |

